  "decision_conditions": [
    "Reason : 1 - The proposed development by reason of its height, scale, bulk and proportions fails to; i) respect the form, scale, bulk and proportions of the original building and ii) to enhance the local context and contribute positively to the character and appearance of the wider built environment contrary to London Plan 2021 Policy D3, Merton Sites and Policies Plan (2014) policies  DMD1, DMD2 & DM D3 and Merton Core Strategy (2011) policy CS14",
    "Reason : 2 - The size, siting and design of the proposed development would represent an overly dominant, visually intrusive and unneighbourly form of development that would result in overshadowing and a loss of light, privacy and outlook to the material detriment of the amenity of neighbouring residents contrary to London Plan (2021) policy D3, policy CS14 of the Merton LDF Core Planning Strategy (2011) and policy DM D2 of the Merton Sites and Policies Plan (2014).",
    "Reason : 3 - The applicant has failed to demonstrate that i) the proposed development will not adversely affect the structural stability of the culvert that encompasses a large section of the site and ii) that flood risk will not be increased elsewhere as a result of the proposed development, contrary to Para 159 of the NPPF 2019 and policy SI 12 of the London Plan 2021. ",
    "Reason : 4 - INFORMATIVE\r\nNote to Applicant\r\n In accordance with paragraph 38 of the NPPF, The London Borough of Merton  (LBM) takes a positive and proactive approach to development proposals focused on solutions. LBM works with applicants/agents in a positive and proactive manner by:\r\n\"\tOffering a pre-application advice and duty desk service. \r\n\"\tWhere possible, suggesting solutions to secure a successful outcome.\r\n\"\tAs appropriate, updating applicants/agents of any issues that may arise in the processing of their application.\r\nIn this instance:\r\n\"\tThe applicant/agent was informed of any issues arising during consideration of the application and how these could potentially be overcome but sufficient information was not forthcoming. \r\n\"\tThe application was considered to be fundamentally contrary to the provisions of the Development Plan and the NPPF, and there were not considered to be any solutions to resolve this conflict. \r\n\"\tIt is noted that the applicant/agent did not engage in any pre-application discussions.\r\n\"\tThe applicant is advised to seek pre-application advice on any resubmission.\r\n"
  ],
